thread2 acquires A's RLatch(Optimistic strategy), acquires C's WLatch, and releases A's RLatch
thread1 does leaf node scan from right to left, trys to acquire C's RLatch and fails
Although we know C's WLatch will eventually be released by thread2, and it seems that thread1 can wait for it,

ol.li: thread1 knows nothing about who take C's WLatch and what it is doing, so he cannot keep waiting.

li.span: thread1 can wait for a period of time and retry, then terminate and redo if it fails to acquire C's RLatch.
